```json
{
  "application": "Quantum ESPRESSO",
  "details": {
    "modules": [
      "DL-CondaPy/3.7",
      "oneapi/compiler/2022.0.2",
      "oneapi/mpi/2021.5.1",
      "QE-oneapi-compiler/7.1"
    ],
    "resources": {
      "partition": "small",
      "nodes": 3,
      "tasks_per_node": 48,
      "scratch_folder": "//scratch/$USER"
    },
    "environment": {
      "setup_env_script": "/home/apps/spack/share/spack/setup-env.sh",
      "oneapi_setvars_script": "/opt/ohpc/pub/intel/oneapi/setvars.sh"
    }
  }
}
```

This script runs the **Quantum ESPRESSO** application, a software package for electronic structure calculations. It uses various modules for Python, Intel oneAPI compiler and MPI libraries, and the Quantum ESPRESSO package itself. The script also uses several resources including a specific partition, a specified number of nodes and tasks per node, and a scratch folder for temporary files. Finally, it includes environment setup scripts for both spack and Intel oneAPI.
